Program: Last Word
Title: Lynda Bellingham, Ben Bradlee, Geoffrey Perry, John Holt
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04m3jd0
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 26 Oct 2014
Andrea Catherwood on: Lynda Bellingham, a much loved actress, best known as the gravy making mum in Oxo television ads. Ben Bradlee, charismatic editor of the Washington Post, at the helm of the paper when it broke the Watergate scandal which brought down President Nixon. John Holt, the honey voiced Jamaican reggae artist and songwriter. Geoffrey Perry, a Berlin born Jew who became an officer in the British army and captured Lord Haw Haw, the Nazi propaganda broadcaster, at the end of the war. Show less